docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON -- The Federal Government has no power to redesign the nation's health care system; nor can it compel all the nation's hospitals, doctors and purveyors of drugs to limit their charges. The Government probably would be reluctant to use such power if it could.

docs.lead_paragraph: KALAMAZOO, Mich, July 11 (AP) -- The Upjohn Company won today an order from the United States District Court keeping its Panalba combination antibiotic products on the market pending further administrative action.
